parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turbo resonator can cause sudden and complete loss of engine power, leading to a significant safety hazard, especially when driving on highways or steep inclines.
The sudden loss of engine power can cause accidents, especially when driving on highways or steep inclines, and can lead to a safety hazard for the driver and other road users.
The failure to address emissions recall issues can lead to carbon monoxide fumes entering the cabin, setting off carbon monoxide alarms, and causing a safety hazard for the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Carbon monoxide fumes entering the cabin
and black smoke coming out of the exhaust pipe.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended movement of the vehicle can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle rolls down a hill or into traffic.
symptoms: The gear shifter can be moved from park to neutral without the keys in the ignition or the "bypass" switch being pressed
allowing the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is traveling at high speeds on expressways.
symptoms: The engine stops working while driving
and may require an engine replacement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and limp mode can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle suddenly loses power and speed on highways.
symptoms: The vehicle may go into limp mode
causing the RPMs to rise without corresponding acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turbo resonator can cause a sudden loss of power and speed, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially on highways.
symptoms: causing an immediate loss of power and speed

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to address emissions system recalls can lead to environmental concerns and potential registration issues.
symptoms: Vehicle owners receive recall notices for emissions control device issues
but face difficulties in getting the recall work done due to dealerships no longer servicing the vehicle model.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turbo resonator can cause a sudden and unsafe drop in uphill speed, particularly in interstate and mountainous travel, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The turbo resonator fails without warning
resulting in a sharp loss of power and speed
especially when driving uphill or in mountainous areas.
